JDK 
JDK stands for "Java Development Kit" and which has the following subcomponents.
1 - Java Compiler
2 - JVM
3 - JavaLib

1 - Java Compiler
Java Compiler will compile the Source code and generate Byte code when the compilation is successful.

2 - JVM
JVM stands for "Java Virtual Machine" and which is used to execute byte code.
The software component which internally having behaviour like machine is known as virtual machine.

3 - JavaLib
JavaLib will provide pre-defined ready constructed components which are used in application development.

JRE
JRE stands for "Java Run-time Environment" and whichc is an execution environment of JDK.
JRE is collection of JVM and JavaLib.

JVM
JVM is part of JRE
